Fantastic Beasts and Where to Find Them
Recently, a Weibo user claimed to be a doctor of virology at North Carolina State University, saying that he was infected with different strains twice in five days, which attracted a lot of patriotic big Vs to repost. He also said that Paxiovid was a failed project during his doctoral studies, and that the United States was promoting traditional Chinese medicine.
After investigation by the public security organs, it was found that the person's real identity was an employee of a convenience store, and he was punished with administrative detention.
